replies.body:
I guess its a bit too much like, they could have decreased his damage, made his cool downs or mana cost higher. I am very puzzled why they'd hit the the ult so hard, I guess everyone was sick of him jumping on carries and blowing them up, but I don't see Kassadin as much of a burst mage his role is also another doozy. The problem I find is, that they nerfed the damage on his q and then they reduce the ults range and all that is done in return is lowering the stacking mana cost but by simple math this only means that you'll be able to ult and extra 1 or 2 times. Another champ burned.

-Kyuubix, Happy Nerfmas everybody.

